ely caused by stellar\nlight scattered by dust. Conclusions. The two spiral arms are at different\nseparation from the star, have very different pitch angles, and are separated\nby an apparent discontinuity, suggesting they might have a different origin.\nThe very open southern spiral arm might be caused by infalling material from\nlate encounters with cloudlets into the formation environment of the star\nitself. The compact feature could be caused by interaction with a planet in\nformation still embedded in its dust envelope and it could be responsible for\nlaunching the north-east spiral. We estimate a mass of the putative embedded\nobject of the order of few M_Jup .\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 2 Nov 2021 16:09:46 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-02-02"}
