{"id":"2111.02174","submitter":"Nils M\\\"uller","authors":"Nils M\\\"uller, Carsten Heinrich, Kai Heussen, Henrik W. Bindner","title":"Unsupervised detection and open-set classification of fast-ramped\n  flexibility activation events","comments":"Published in Applied Energy and open access available at\n  https://doi.org/10.1016/j.apenergy.2022.118647","journal-ref":"Mueller, N., Heinrich, C., Heussen, K., & Bindner, H. W. (2022).\n  Unsupervised detection and open-set classification of fast-ramped flexibility\n  activation events. Applied Energy, 312","doi":"10.1016/j.apenergy.2022.118647","report-no":null,"categories":"eess.SY cs.SY stat.ML","license":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","abstract":"  The continuous electrification of the mobility and heating sectors adds\nmuch-needed flexibility to the power system. However, flexibility utilization\nalso introduces new challenges to distribution system operators (DSOs), who\nneed mechanisms to supervise flexibility activations and monitor their effect\non distribution network operation. Flexibility activations can be broadly\ncategorized to those originating from electricity markets and those initiated\nby the DSO to avoid constraint violations. Simultaneous electricity market\ndriven flexibility activations may cause voltage quality or temporary\noverloading issues, and the failure of flexibility activations initiated by the\nDSO might leave critical grid states unresolved. This work proposes a novel\ndata processing pipeline for automated real-time identification of fast-ramped\nflexibility activation events. Its practical value is twofold: i) potentially\ncritical flexibility activations originating from electricity markets can be\ndetected by the DSO at an early stage, and ii) successful activation of\nDSO-requested flexibility can be verified by the operator. In both cases the\nincreased awareness would allow the DSO to take counteractions to avoid\npotentially critical grid situations. The proposed pipeline combines techniques\nfrom unsupervised detection and open-set classification. For both building\nblocks feasibility is systematically evaluated and proofed on real load and\nflexibility activation data.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 Nov 2021 12:29:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 1 Dec 2021 08:19:46 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 4 Mar 2022 13:19:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-07"}
